SIMPLE: underpin
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Underpin
<hw>Un`der*pin"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Underpinned</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Underpinning</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To lay
stones, masonry, etc., under, as the sills of a building, on which it is
to rest.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To support by some solid foundation; to place
something underneath for support.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Underpinning</ent>⟦br⟧
